The Vice President, Joe Biden, released a statement expressing his sadness over the passing of Howard Baker. He described Baker as a friend and praised his accomplishments as an ambassador, White House Chief of Staff, and Senate Majority Leader. Biden highlighted Baker's integrity, wisdom, and ability to find honorable compromises. He also mentioned their collaboration on significant legislation and their friendship over the years. Biden acknowledged Baker's role in passing important acts, such as the Clean Air Act and the Clean Water Act, as well as his involvement in the Watergate Committee and the Panama Canal Treaty. He emphasized Baker's ability to understand different viewpoints and work towards peaceful resolutions. In conclusion, Biden described Baker as a good man who made the country and the world a better place.